	"\e[0mThe purpose of learning is growth, and our minds, unlike our bodies, can continue growing as we continue to live.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMortimer Adler\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen you realize how perfect everything is you will tilt your head back and laugh at the sky.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mFor every failure, there's an alternative course of action. You just have to find it. When you come to a roadblock, take a detour.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMary Kay Ash\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIt is surprising what a man can do when he has to, and how little most men will do when they don't have to.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWalter Linn\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo be aware of a single shortcoming in oneself is more useful than to be aware of a thousand in someone else.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mTenzin Gyatso\e[0m"
	"\e[0mNobody made a greater mistake than he who did nothing because he could do only a little.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mEdmund Burke\e[0m"
	"\e[0mConstant kindness can accomplish much. As the sun makes ice melt, kindness causes misunderstanding, mistrust, and hostility to evaporate.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Schweitzer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe greatest minds are capable of the greatest vices as well as of the greatest virtues.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRene Descartes\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA man should look for what is, and not for what he thinks should be.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Einstein\e[0m"
	"\e[0mDifficulties are meant to rouse, not discourage. The human spirit is to grow strong by conflict.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWilliam Channing\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf you have no respect for your own values how can you be worthy of respect from others.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mByron Pulsifer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSome people are always grumbling because roses have thorns; I am thankful that thorns have roses.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlphonse Karr\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo choose what is difficult all ones days, as if it were easy, that is faith.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mW. H. Auden\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAbility is what you're capable of doing. Motivation determines what you do.Attitude determines how well you do it.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mLou Holtz\e[0m"
	"\e[0mDo not be embarrassed by your mistakes. Nothing can teach us better than our understanding of them. This is one of the best ways of self-education.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mThomas Carlyle\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThousands of candles can be lighted from a single candle, and the life of the candle will not be shortened. Happiness never decreases by being shared.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mI care not so much what I am to others as what I am to myself. I will be rich by myself, and not by borrowing.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMichel de Montaigne\e[0m"
	"\e[0mKnow that although in the eternal scheme of things you are small, you are also unique and irreplaceable, as are all your fellow humans everywhere in the world.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMargaret Laurence\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo do all that one is able to do, is to be a man; to do all that one would like to do, is to be a god.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mNapoleon Bonaparte\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf you let go a little, you will have a little peace. If you let go a lot, you will have a lot of peace.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAjahn Chah\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThere is no need for temples, no need for complicated philosophies. My brain and my heart are my temples; my philosophy is kindness.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDalai Lama\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe spirit, the will to win, and the will to excel, are the things that endure. These qualities are so much more important than the events that occur.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mVincent Lombardi\e[0m"
	"\e[0mMan is not sum of what he has already, but rather the sum of what he does not yet have, of what he could have.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJean-Paul Sartre\e[0m"
	"\e[0mDon't believe what your eyes are telling you. All they show is limitation. Look with your understanding, find out what you already know, and you'll see the way to fly.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRichard Bach\e[0m"
	"\e[0mI believe that we are solely responsible for our choices, and we have to accept the consequences of every deed, word, and thought throughout our lifetime.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mElisabeth Kubler-Ross\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWishes can be your best avenue of getting what you want when you turn wishes into action. Action moves your wish to the forefront from thought to reality.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mByron Pulsifer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo understand the heart and mind of a person, look not at what he has already achieved, but at what he aspires to do.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mKahlil Gibran\e[0m"
	"\e[0mI am of the opinion that my life belongs to the community, and as long as I live it is my privilege to do for it whatever I can.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBernard Shaw\e[0m"
	"\e[0mImagination is more important than knowledge. For while knowledge defines all we currently know and understand, imagination points to all we might yet discover and create.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Einstein\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen you see a good person, think of becoming like him. When you see someone not so good, reflect on your own weak points.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mConfucius\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf one is estranged from oneself, then one is estranged from others too. If one is out of touch with oneself, then one cannot touch others.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAnne Lindbergh\e[0m"
	"\e[0mMost of the important things in the world have been accomplished by people who have kept on trying when there seemed to be no hope at all.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDale Carnegie\e[0m"
	"\e[0mYou may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one, I hope someday you will join us, and the world will live as one.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJohn Lennon\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHappiness is as a butterfly which, when pursued, is always beyond our grasp, but which if you will sit down quietly, may alight upon you.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mNathaniel Hawthorne\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHe who experiences the unity of life sees his own Self in all beings, and all beings in his own Self, and looks on everything with an impartial eye.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIn the sky, there is no distinction of east and west; people create distinctions out of their own minds and then believe them to be true.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mYou cannot change anything in your life with intention alone, which can become a watered-down, occasional hope that you'll get to tomorrow. Intention without action is useless.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCaroline Myss\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBefore you can inspire with emotion, you must be swamped with it yourself. Before you can move their tears, your own must flow. To convince them, you must yourself believe.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWinston Churchill\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe greatest discovery of our generation is that human beings can alter their lives by altering their attitudes of mind. As you think, so shall you be.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWilliam James\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf one advances confidently in the direction of his dream, and endeavours to live the life which he had imagines, he will meet with a success unexpected in common hours.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mHenry David Thoreau\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe secret of joy in work is contained in one word excellence. To know how to do something well is to enjoy it.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mPearl Buck\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen you meet someone better than yourself, turn your thoughts to becoming his equal. When you meet someone not as good as you are, look within and examine your own self.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mConfucius\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWe must overcome the notion that we must be regular. It robs you of the chance to be extraordinary and leads you to the mediocre.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mUta Hagen\e[0m"
	"\e[0mMost of our obstacles would melt away if, instead of cowering before them, we should make up our minds to walk boldly through them.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mOrison Marden\e[0m"
	"\e[0mEverything can be taken from a man but ... the last of the human freedoms to choose ones attitude in any given set of circumstances, to choose ones own way.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mVictor Frankl\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIt is better to have enough ideas for some of them to be wrong, than to be always right by having no ideas at all.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mEdward de Bono\e[0m"
	"\e[0mCharacter is like a tree and reputation like a shadow. The shadow is what we think of it; the tree is the real thing.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAbraham Lincoln\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBy letting it go it all gets done. The world is won by those who let it go. But when you try and try. The world is beyond the winning.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mLao Tzu\e[0m"
	"\e[0mI am like a falling star who has finally found her place next to another in a lovely constellation, where we will sparkle in the heavens forever.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAmy Tan\e[0m"
	"\e[0mNot every difficult and dangerous thing is suitable for training, but only that which is conducive to success in achieving the object of our effort.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mEpictetus\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWe are not animals. We are not a product of what has happened to us in our past. We have the power of choice.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mStephen Covey\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe most dangerous way to lose time is not to spend it having fun, but to spend it doing fake work. When you spend time having fun, you know you're being self-indulgent.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mPaul Graham\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThousands of candles can be lit from a single, and the life of the candle will not be shortened. Happiness never decreases by being shared.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA lot of times people look at the negative side of what they feel they can't do. I always look on the positive side of what I can do.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mChuck Norris\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWithout passion man is a mere latent force and possibility, like the flint which awaits the shock of the iron before it can give forth its spark.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAmiel\e[0m"
	"\e[0mLove at first sight is easy to understand; its when two people have been looking at each other for a lifetime that it becomes a miracle.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAmy Bloom\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWith courage you will dare to take risks, have the strength to be compassionate, and the wisdom to be humble. Courage is the foundation of integrity.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mKeshavan Nair\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe right way is not always the popular and easy way. Standing for right when it is unpopular is a true test of moral character.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMargaret Smith\e[0m"
	"\e[0mI prefer to be true to myself, even at the hazard of incurring the ridicule of others, rather than to be false, and to incur my own abhorrence.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mFrederick Douglass\e[0m"
	"\e[0mNo pessimist ever discovered the secrets of the stars, or sailed to an uncharted land, or opened a new heaven to the human spirit.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mHelen Keller\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen you arise in the morning, think of what a precious privilege it is to be alive to breathe, to think, to enjoy, to love.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMarcus Aurelius\e[0m"
	"\e[0mCharacter cannot be developed in ease and quiet. Only through experience of trial and suffering can the soul be strengthened, vision cleared, ambition inspired, and success achieved.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mHelen Keller\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAlthough there may be tragedy in your life, there's always a possibility to triumph. It doesn't matter who you are, where you come from. The ability to triumph begins with you. Always.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mOprah Winfrey\e[0m"
	"\e[0mYou must train your intuition you must trust the small voice inside you which tells you exactly what to say, what to decide.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mIngrid Bergman\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAccept the things to which fate binds you, and love the people with whom fate brings you together, but do so with all your heart.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMarcus Aurelius\e[0m"
	"\e[0mLet us resolve to be masters, not the victims, of our history, controlling our own destiny without giving way to blind suspicions and emotions.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJohn Kennedy\e[0m"
	"\e[0mNothing in life is to be feared, it is only to be understood. Now is the time to understand more, so that we may fear less.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMarie Curie\e[0m"
	"\e[0mParents can only give good advice or put them on the right paths, but the final forming of a persons character lies in their own hands.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAnne Frank\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAdversity isn't set against you to fail; adversity is a way to build your character so that you can succeed over and over again through perseverance.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mByron Pulsifer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf you break your neck, if you have nothing to eat, if your house is on fire, then you got a problem. Everything else is inconvenience.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRobert Fulghum\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSuccess is not the key to happiness. Happiness is the key to success. If you love what you are doing, you will be successful.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Schweitzer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf A is success in life, then A equals x plus y plus z. Work is x; y is play; and z is keeping your mouth shut.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Einstein\e[0m"
	"\e[0mMy advice to you is not to inquire why or whither, but just enjoy your ice cream while its on your plate that's my philosophy.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mThornton Wilder\e[0m"
	"\e[0mConflict is the gadfly of thought. It stirs us to observation and memory. It instigates to invention. It shocks us out of sheeplike passivity, and sets us at noting and contriving.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJohn Dewey\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHe who conquers others is strong; He who conquers himself is mighty.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mLao Tzu\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAnything you really want, you can attain, if you really go after it.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWayne Dyer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mArriving at one point is the starting point to another.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJohn Dewey\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe foolish man seeks happiness in the distance, the wise grows it under his feet.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJames Oppenheim\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe greatest part of our happiness depends on our dispositions, not our circumstances.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMartha Washington\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIt is only possible to live happily ever after on a day to day basis.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMargaret Bonnano\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA man sees in the world what he carries in his heart.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mGoethe\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAction may not always bring happiness, but there is no happiness without action.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBenjamin Disraeli\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBelieve deep down in your heart that you're destined to do great things.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJoe Paterno\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSooner or later, those who win are those who think they can.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRichard Bach\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe only limit to your impact is your imagination and commitment.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mTony Robbins\e[0m"
	"\e[0mYou are special, you are unique, you are the best!\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCathy Pulsifer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mFour steps to achievement: Plan purposefully. Prepare prayerfully. Proceed positively. Pursue persistently.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWilliam Arthur Ward\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo know oneself is to study oneself in action with another person.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBruce Lee\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWe must not allow ourselves to become like the system we oppose.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBishop Desmond Tutu\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSmile, breathe and go slowly.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mThich Nhat Hanh\e[0m"
	"\e[0mReality is merely an illusion, albeit a very persistent one.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Einstein\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen you come to the end of your rope, tie a knot and hang on.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mFranklin Roosevelt\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAlways be mindful of the kindness and not the faults of others.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mEverything that irritates us about others can lead us to an understanding of ourselves.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCarl Jung\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen fate hands us a lemon, lets try to make lemonade.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDale Carnegie\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe weak can never forgive. Forgiveness is the attribute of the strong.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMohandas Gandhi\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA man is great by deeds, not by birth.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mChanakya\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSuccess is getting what you want. Happiness is wanting what you get.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDale Carnegie\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTruth isn't all about what actually happens but more about how what has happened is interpreted.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mByron Pulsifer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA good rest is half the work.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mnull\e[0m"
	"\e[0mDon't judge each day by the harvest you reap but by the seeds that you plant.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRobert Stevenson\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSmall opportunities are often the beginning of great enterprises.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDemosthenes\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo be tested is good. The challenged life may be the best therapist.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mGail Sheehy\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTake heed: you do not find what you do not seek.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mEnglish proverb\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHappiness is the reward we get for living to the highest right we know.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRichard Bach\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBe slow of tongue and quick of eye.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCervantes\e[0m"
	"\e[0mFreedom is not worth having if it does not connote freedom to err.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMohandas Gandhi\e[0m"
	"\e[0mI have always thought the actions of men the best interpreters of their thoughts.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJohn Locke\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHe who obtains has little. He who scatters has much.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mLao Tzu\e[0m"
	"\e[0mTo dare is to lose ones footing momentarily. To not dare is to lose oneself.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mSoren Kierkegaard\e[0m"
	"\e[0mNo day in which you learn something is a complete loss.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDavid Eddings\e[0m"
	"\e[0mPeace cannot be kept by force. It can only be achieved by understanding.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Einstein\e[0m"
	"\e[0mReal success is finding your lifework in the work that you love.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDavid McCullough\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBetter than a thousand hollow words, is one word that brings peace.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAll the flowers of all the tomorrows are in the seeds of today.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mnull\e[0m"
	"\e[0mYour sacred space is where you can find yourself again and again.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mJoseph Campbell\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAs you think, so shall you become.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBruce Lee\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIn seed time learn, in harvest teach, in winter enjoy.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWilliam Blake\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHappiness does not come from having much, but from being attached to little.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCheng Yen\e[0m"
	"\e[0mEvery gift from a friend is a wish for your happiness.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRichard Bach\e[0m"
	"\e[0mGo put your creed into the deed. Nor speak with double tongue.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRalph Emerson\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe wisest men follow their own direction.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mEuripides\e[0m"
	"\e[0mHope arouses, as nothing else can arouse, a passion for the possible.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWilliam Sloane Coffin\e[0m"
	"\e[0mEverything has beauty, but not everyone sees it.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mConfucius\e[0m"
	"\e[0mNothing ever goes away until it has taught us what we need to know.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mPema Chodron\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhen you learn, teach. When you get, give.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMaya Angelou\e[0m"
	"\e[0mOnly when we are no longer afraid do we begin to live.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDorothy Thompson\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIf you smile when no one else is around, you really mean it.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAndy Rooney\e[0m"
	"\e[0mLove is the only force capable of transforming an enemy into friend.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMartin Luther King, Jr.\e[0m"
	"\e[0mIn all chaos there is a cosmos, in all disorder a secret order.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCarl Jung\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA man is not where he lives but where he loves.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mnull\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe price of greatness is responsibility.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWinston Churchill\e[0m"
	"\e[0mDecision is a risk rooted in the courage of being free.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mPaul Tillich\e[0m"
	"\e[0mYour mind will answer most questions if you learn to relax and wait for the answer.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWilliam Burroughs\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe world does not happen to you it happens from you.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mnull\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWe cannot solve our problems with the same thinking we used when we created them.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlbert Einstein\e[0m"
	"\e[0mMore powerful than the will to win is the courage to begin.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mnull\e[0m"
	"\e[0mLearning is finding out what you already know.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRichard Bach\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSaying thank you is more than good manners. It is good spirituality.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAlfred Painter\e[0m"
	"\e[0mSilence is a source of great strength.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mLao Tzu\e[0m"
	"\e[0mJoy is the best makeup.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mAnne Lamott\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThere is no great genius without some touch of madness.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mSeneca\e[0m"
	"\e[0mA jug fills drop by drop.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mBuddha\e[0m"
	"\e[0mUntil you make peace with who you are, you'll never be content with what you have.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mDoris Mortman\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWe aim above the mark to hit the mark.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRalph Emerson\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBeing angry never solves anything.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCatherine Pulsifer\e[0m"
	"\e[0mAll men who have achieved great things have been great dreamers.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mOrison Marden\e[0m"
	"\e[0mMediocrity knows nothing higher than itself, but talent instantly recognizes genius.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mArthur Conan Doyle\e[0m"
	"\e[0mWhere all think alike, no one thinks very much.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mWalter Lippmann\e[0m"
	"\e[0mEverything that exists is in a manner the seed of that which will be.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMarcus Aurelius\e[0m"
	"\e[0mBe less curious about people and more curious about ideas.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mMarie Curie\e[0m"
	"\e[0mThe heart has eyes which the brain knows nothing of.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mCharles Perkhurst\e[0m"
	"\e[0mOnly those who dare to fail greatly can ever achieve greatly.\n\t\e[1m\e[96mRobert Kennedy\e[0m"
